{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01NxrQk7SXofWSRvS3tDmeh9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The old pod finished terminating on its own. Everything is now clean and stable:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` (the credentials `app-producer` uses) had permissions granted on `/app` for `write`/`read` but an empty `configure` permission, so it was refused when trying to declare `app-queue` (`not_authorised`).\n\n**Fix:** `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — restored full configure/write/read permissions for `app-user` on the `/app` vhost (no data loss, no CRDs/operators involved).\n\n**Verified:**\n- `app-producer` pod is `1/1 Running`/Ready, no crash loop.\n- `/app` vhost has `app-queue` (type `classic`) with messages accumulating (17+ and growing).\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) are running and clustered (`cluster_status` shows all 3 as disk + running nodes)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":501,"cache_read_input_tokens":47215,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":501},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0144ed0e-e15a-436b-aa0b-063d6203f26d","uuid":"59e728e0-1c72-4e51-a15c-15f684e8a840","request_id":"req_011CcaqYg8kgPNEsEk9S8PpD"}
